body: Why was it working so well for so long? Did I just luck out?
I have no idea - I thought it was always the case that RTX cards don't run face extraction with this software. Hopefully someone else can comment.

i have no RTX 2080 TI , cannot say anything. 
I am planning to support RTX when tf 1.13 (not rc) will be released

@Mjolnir343, just to clarify, you were able to extract with your rig before you moved to a new apartment, and now extract doesn't work?  Did you download a newer build of DFL or upgrade your video driver?  If all physical connections are OK (GPUs or power connectors have been jostled slightly in the move), then check your disk drive for errors.

@gessyoo, correct. Everything was fine before the move. I've made several SNL deepfake videos for the r/GifFakes subreddit, and they turned out very nicely. I haven't had a single odd message or error in the couple of months I've been playing with the tool.

I checked all the physical connections visually. I have a rigid tubing LCS setup, so I didn't re-seat either of the cards. My drives are M.2 SSDs, so they should have weathered any rough handling, but I'll run some diagnostics anyways. They're held in place with a screw and under a heatsink, so I didn't check them visually.

I've since run a bunch of benchmarks and even reinstalled Windows, but it still isn't working. My computer was offline for about a week during the move, so there were definitely some driver updates in Nvidia GeForce Experience when I got everything set back up at the new place. 

At this point, it looks like new drivers popped whatever bubble of stability I was in. I've never tried to roll back drivers before, but it doesn't look very difficult. I'll try that next.
Well, rolling back the GPU drivers to their previous state didn't change a thing. I guess I'm just gonna have to be patient and hope that tensorflow 1.13 fixes the problem, whatever the problem is.

Question: I ran the MT extractor with the --cpu-only argument, but it still throws a mess of errors and crashes by the 2nd pass. If my issue is a RTX/CUDA 10 issue, why doesn't the CPU only extractor work?
@Mjolnir343, the DeepFaceLab torrent has a separate CPU installation for CPU-only, look for a file named "DeepFaceLabCPUTorrent ---.zip" in the torrent download location.
@gessyoo, Roger that. Thanks for the heads up.
